  "prompt": "Why was the Pakistan national anthem sung first in the India-Pakistan World Cup match?",
  "response": "In international sports events, it is customary to follow certain protocols, which include the playing of national anthems before the start of a match. The sequence in which the anthems are played often follows specific traditions or established norms.\n\nFor cricket matches, including high-profile tournaments like the ICC Cricket World Cup, the order in which the national anthems are played typically follows the convention where the visiting team's anthem is played first, followed by the host team's anthem. In the case of the India-Pakistan World Cup match, if Pakistan was considered the visiting team, their anthem would be played first, followed by India's anthem.\n\nThese practices are part of the broader tradition of sportsmanship and respect, ensuring that both teams are acknowledged appropriately before the competition begins.",
